---
import image3 from "../../../assets/image_3.jpg";
---

<section class="w-full py-24 md:py-32 px-8 md:px-16 lg:px-24 bg-[#f4f6f8]">
  <div
    class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 md:gap-24 items-center"
  >
    <div class="flex flex-col">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-[54px] text-[#1e293b] tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-8"
        style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;"
      >
        Beautiful Because It Broke
      </h2>
      <p
        class="text-[#64748b] text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[1.8] font-light mb-6"
      >
        There is a Japanese word — <em>wabi-sabi</em> — for the beauty found in
        things that are cracked, weathered, and incomplete. De Aurimori does not
        hide its fractures. It builds around them. The imperfection is not a flaw
        to be corrected — it is the only honest part of the whole.
      </p>
      <p
        class="text-[#64748b] text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[1.8] font-light"
      >
        A sharp edge against a worn surface. A clean line running through
        something that has clearly been through time. This is not contradiction —
        it is the only kind of beauty that does not lie about what it has
        survived.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="relative w-full aspect-[4/3] md:aspect-square ml-auto">
      <div
        class="absolute -inset-4 md:-top-6 md:-right-6 md:bottom-6 md:left-6 border border-[#c2e8f6] z-0"
      >
      </div>
      <img
        src={image3.src}
        alt="Organic abstract texture"
        class="relative z-10 w-full h-full object-cover grayscale opacity-95"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>